title: Police Release Images of 2 Individuals Seen Near a Baltimore Homicide
text:
Police Release Images of 2 Individuals Seen Near a Baltimore Homicide February 11, 2017 3:55 PM 
BALTIMORE (WJZ)â€“ City police are continuing to investigate a homicide that occurred on Thursday in the 200 block of North Hilton Street. 
Detectives are attempting to identify two individuals who were seen in the area. 
RELATED: Man Dies After Shooting in Southwest Baltimore 
At about 2:50 p.m., police located 21-year old Deontae Bluefort with gunshot wounds to his body. 
Anyone with information on the identify of these individuals is asked to call detectives at 410-396-2100 or you can text tips to 443-902-4824.
